Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC8se.name: setValue(_:forKey:)
Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC8se.abstract: Sets the value of the key. Before setting, the old value is removed. So if you want to delete the key, just set its value to nil.

Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC8ge.name: getValue(forKey:)
Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC8ge.abstract: Returns the value of the key or nil, if the key does not exist.

Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC9se.name: setSecKey(_:forKey:)
Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC9se.abstract: Saves the SecKey object to the keychain. Before saving, the old value is deleted, So, if you want to delete the item, just set its value to nil.

Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC9ge.name: getSecKey(forKey:)
Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC9ge.abstract: Returns the SecKey object associated with the key or nil, if the key does not exist.

Classes/Keychain.html.name: Keychain
Classes/Keychain.html.abstract: The Keychain class makes it easy to work with items in the keychain storage.
